      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAC BON (4) is an accomplished pacer who hasn't raced since a brave fifth from a tough draw in the Breeders Crown Final at Melton in December. Strikes at 50 per cent at the mile and should be ready to go off a couple of trials. LOUIE LOU I NZ (3) has the hoof on the till after seconds from wide barriers in his two outings at this circuit and distance since switching from Victoria. Better drawn tonight so could break through. Dual Group 1 winner SOHO AMERICANO (1) is much better served by the inside draw having come from the extreme outside first up. Has recorded two wins and two placings in four second-up attempts so should be improved. CHICAGO BART (6) is in good form having won three of his last four starts, one of them from a similar draw over this circuit and distance. SNAP SHOT NZ (2) is racing well and draws to advantage so could play a role.",
